    <documentation>
      ##################################################################################
      Hardware setup
      ##################################################################################
      The Triad 8-Zone Power Amplifier Installation Guide contains all necessary hardware setup information.
      For the installation guide, go to http://triadspkrs.co/8zamp-ig

      ##################################################################################
      Driver setup and properties
      ##################################################################################
      Driver Version
      This field displays the current driver version number.

      Zone Output/Linked Input Settings
      This section identifies whether an amplifier output/zone is linked to a zone input or the global input.
      By default, each amplifier output/zone is linked one-to-one with its respective zone input.  For example,
      whatever is connected to Zone Input 2 will output on Zone Output 2.  However, each amplifier output can
      be linked instead to Global In.  For more information, see the â€œGlobal In/Zone Input 1â€ section below.

      Debug Mode
      This section enables varying levels of logging for the Triad 8-Zone Power Amplifier.

      ##################################################################################
      Power Off Delay Timer
      ##################################################################################
      A power off delay timer exists which will keep the device on for the number of seconds set in the properties page,
      after the device is told to turn off when using a relay for power control.  Use this setting if the end of
      announcements or other media is getting cut off due to the amp getting turned off too soon.  This value is in seconds.

      ##################################################################################
      Bindings (Connections)
      ##################################################################################
      Using Composer, click on the connections tab in the left pane, then select the Triad 8-Zone Power Amplifier
      driver in the project in which bindings will be set up.

      1.  Bind the inputs of the 8-Zone Power Amplifier to the outputs of an Audio Matrix Switch (AMS), or other
      device, which produces audio.
      2.  If using the 12V trigger output of a Triad AMS to wake up the amplifier, bind the 12V Trigger In of the
      8-Zone Power Amplifier to the 12V Trigger Out of the Triad AMS.  Also, ensure the physical Power Mode
      switch on the 8-Zone Power Amplifier is in the 12V position.
      3.  Bind the Audio End Point of rooms in the project to the Room End Points on the 8-Zone Power Amplifier.
      4.  Bind the Audio Volume of rooms in the project to the Audio Volume control of the AMS, or other device,
      which produces audio.  Note: If you do not bind the Audio Volume to the AMS or device producing the
      audio you will not have volume control.

      ##################################################################################
      Using a Control4 Controller or I/O Extender Relay For Power Control
      ##################################################################################
      A relay from a Control4 controller or I/O extender can be used to power on the amplifier. The relay will close when
      the amplifier needs to be turned on, and this will trigger the amplifier to power up.

      1. Connect the signal wire (tip of the 3.5mm connector connected to the amplifier) to the NO of a relay block
      on a Control4 controller or I/O extender.
      2. Connect the ground (sleeve of the 3.5mm connector connected to the amplifier) to the GND of a contact block
      of the controller or I/O extender.
      3. Connect the +12V of a contact block to the COM of a relay block on the controller or I/O extender.

      * Note : You must have the Power Mode switch set to 12V setting.
      * Note : Do not bind or wire, multiple amplifiers to a single relay.  Doing this will cause both amplifiers to turn on
      and off at the same time, regardless of what zones are in use.

      For further information regarding using a Controller or I/O extender relay for power control, view this knowledgebase
      article - ctrl4.co/12vtrigger

      ##################################################################################
      Audio 1/ Global Input
      ##################################################################################
      The Global Input connection on the Triad 4-Zone Power Amplifier is shared with Zone Input 1.  If the global
      input needs to be linked to any amplifier output other than Zone Output 1, you must physically toggle the
      â€œLink To Global Inputâ€ dipswitch for each amplifier output.  If you wish to have all amplifier outputs
      connected to the global input, you can flip on (up position) the â€œAllâ€ dipswitch.  Once the dipswitch settings
      have been completed, set each input that is assigned to the global input as â€œGlobal Inâ€ in the driver properties.
      Otherwise leave the input set to the Zone Input.

      Prior driver versions had a serperate Global Input.  This connection has been hidden (but still valid for existing
      installs).  Rebind the prior device's binding to the Audio 1/ Global Input or remove and readd to driver if needed
      to adjust prior bindings to the Global Input.

    </documentation>
